A regression analysis between demand (y in 1000 units) and price (x in dollars) resulted in the following equation:

​

= 9 − 3x

​

The above equation implies that if the price is increased by $1, the demand is expected to _____.
increase by 6 units
decrease by 3 units
decrease by 6,000 units
decrease by 3,000 units
Always pay attention to the units.

A regression analysis between sales (in $1000s) and price (in dollars) resulted in the following equation:

​

= 50,000 − 8x

​

The above equation implies that an increase of _____.
$1 in price is associated with a decrease of $8 in sales
$8 in price is associated with an increase of $8,000 in sales
$1 in price is associated with a decrease of $42,000 in sales
$1 in price is associated with a decrease of $8,000 in sales

A regression analysis between sales (y in $1000) and advertising (x in dollars) resulted in the following equation:

     = 50,000 + 6x

​

The above equation implies that an increase of _____.
$6 in advertising is associated with an increase of $6,000 in sales
$1 in advertising is associated with an increase of $6 in sales
$1 in advertising is associated with an increase of $56,000 in sales
$1 in advertising is associated with an increase of $6,000 in sales
If all the points of a scatter diagram lie on the least squares regression line, then the coefficient of determination for these variables based on these data _____.
is 0
is 1
is either 1 or –1, depending upon whether the relationship is positive or negative
could be any value between –1 and 1
In a regression analysis, if r2 = 1, then _____.
SSE must also be equal to 1
SSE must be equal to 0
SSE can be any positive value
SSE must be negative
In regression and correlation analysis, if SSE and SST are known, then with this information the _____.
coefficient of determination can be computed
slope of the line can be computed
y-intercept can be computed
All of the answers are correct.

.600
.166
1.666
.375

.4
.6
.5
.8
In a regression analysis, if SST = 4500 and SSE = 1575, then the coefficient of determination is _____.
.35
.65
2.85
.45
It is possible for the coefficient of determination to be _____.
larger than 1
less than 1
less than 0
All of the answers are correct, depending on the situation under consideration.
If two variables, x and y, have a strong correlation, then _____.
there may or may not be any causal relationship between x and y
x causes y to happen
y causes x to happen
None of the answers is correct.

A data point (observation) that does not fit the trend shown by the remaining data is called a(n) _____.
residual
outlier
point estimate
None of the answers is correct.
In regression analysis, the variable that is being predicted is the _____.
dependent variable
independent variable
intervening variable
None of the answers is correct.
In a regression analysis, the variable that is used to predict the dependent variable ______.
must have the same units as the variable doing the predicting
is the independent variable
is the dependent variable
usually is denoted by x
In regression analysis, if the dependent variable is measured in dollars, the independent variable _____.
must also be in dollars
must be in some unit of currency
can be any units
cannot be in dollars
In regression analysis, the independent variable is typically plotted on the _____.
y-axis of a scatter diagram
x-axis of a scatter diagram
y-axis of a histogram
x-axis of a histogram
A procedure used for finding the equation of a straight line that provides the best fit for the relationship between the independent and dependent variables is ______.
correlation analysis
the mean squares method
the least squares method
the most squares method
Application of the least squares method results in values of the y-intercept and the slope that minimizes the sum of the squared deviations between the _____.
observed values of the independent variable and the predicted values of the independent variable
actual values of the independent variable and the predicted values of the dependent variable
observed values of the dependent variable and the predicted values of the dependent variable
None of the answers is correct.
A least squares regression line ______.
may be used to predict a value of y if the corresponding x value is given
implies a cause-effect relationship between x and y
can only be determined if a good linear relationship exists between x and y
All of the answers are correct.

​

= 80 + 6.2x

​

Based on the above estimated regression line, if advertising is $10,000, then the point estimate for sales (in dollars) is _____.
$62,080
$142,000
$700
$700,000

Regression analysis was applied between sales (in $1000s) and advertising (in $100s), and the following regression function was obtained.

​

= 500 + 4x

​

Based on the above estimated regression line, if advertising is $10,000, then the point estimate for sales (in dollars) is _____.
$900
$900,000
$40,500
$505,000
The equation that describes how the dependent variable (y) is related to the independent variable (x) is called _____.
the correlation model
the regression model
correlation analysis
None of the answers is correct.
In a simple regression analysis (where y is a dependent and x an independent variable), if the y-intercept is positive, then it must be true that _____.
there is a positive correlation between x and y
there is a negative correlation between x and y
if x is increased, y must also increase
None of the answers is correct.
y-intercept does not talk about slope
SSE can never be _____.
larger than SST
smaller than SST
equal to 1
equal to 0
In simple linear regression, r2 is the _____.
estimated regression equation
coefficient of correlation
sum of the squared residuals
coefficient of determination
Larger values of r2 imply that the observations are more closely grouped about the _____.
average value of the independent variables
average value of the dependent variable
least squares line
origin
In a regression analysis, if r2 = 1, then _____.
SSE = SST
SSE = 1
SSR = SSE
SSR = SST
In a regression analysis, if SSE = 200 and SSR = 300, then the coefficient of determination is _____.
.667
.600
.400
1.500
If the coefficient of determination is a positive value, then the regression equation _____.
must have a positive slope
must have a negative slope
could have either a positive or a negative slope
must have a positive y-intercept
r-square talks abou the fit of regression and not the direction of the relationship.
In regression analysis, which of the following is NOT a required assumption about the error term ε?
The expected value of the error term is 0.
The variance of the error term is the same for all values of x.
The values of the error term are independent.
All are required assumptions about the error term.
The proportion of the variation in the dependent variable y that is explained by the estimated regression equation is measured by the _____.
correlation coefficient
standard error of the estimate
coefficient of determination
confidence interval estimate
The difference between the observed value of the dependent variable and the value predicted by using the estimated regression equation is called _____.
the standard error
a residual
a prediction interval
the variance

As the fit for the estimated regression equation increases, the _____.
absolute value of the regression equation’s slope increases
value of the regression equation’s y-intercept decreases
value of the coefficient of determination increases
value of the correlation coefficient increases
Regression analysis is a statistical procedure for developing a mathematical equation that describes how _____.
one independent and one or more dependent variables are related
several independent and several dependent variables are related
one dependent and one or more independent variables are related
None of the answers is correct.
Scatter plots in regression will not tell us exact correlation, but will allow us to infer the direction and probable strength of relationship.
True
False

If the regression has 3 explanatory variables and 100 observations, What will be the degrees of freedom for t-test?
Not enough information
The degrees of freedom for t-test here are n-K-1, where K is the number of explanatory variables. In simple regression K=1, therefore we got the degrees of freedom as n-2.
